1
00:00:00,210 --> 00:00:01,210
(All people, incidents,
and backgrounds...)

2
00:00:01,270 --> 00:00:03,270
(in this drama are fictitious
and unrelated to reality.)

3
00:00:03,340 --> 00:00:05,040
(Also, children were filmed
under production guidelines.)

4
00:00:05,640 --> 00:00:06,810
Goodness, what's going on?

5
00:00:06,950 --> 00:00:09,810
Why was Yu Na here
during work hours?

6
00:00:10,320 --> 00:00:13,250
Goodness, what's with
that look on your face?

7
00:00:14,250 --> 00:00:16,250
- Honey, it's Yu Na.
- Yes?

8
00:00:16,320 --> 00:00:17,660
I think she's...

9
00:00:18,820 --> 00:00:20,460
This is torture.

10
00:00:20,730 --> 00:00:24,130
Cat got your tongue?
Just spit it out.

11
00:00:24,860 --> 00:00:26,700
- Well...
- Yes?

12
00:00:26,770 --> 00:00:29,030
Yu Na ran off with my seal.

13
00:00:29,330 --> 00:00:31,440
What, your seal?

14
00:00:32,070 --> 00:00:33,410
What would she want with it?

15
00:00:34,970 --> 00:00:39,210
She's not in her right mind
since her engagement was called off.

16
00:00:39,780 --> 00:00:41,150
I think she's planning
to sign over our stocks...

17
00:00:41,650 --> 00:00:43,920
to get their approval
for the marriage.

18
00:00:44,580 --> 00:00:46,420
What did you just say?

19
00:00:47,520 --> 00:00:50,960
My gosh. That's just absurd!

20
00:00:51,390 --> 00:00:53,530
Those scoundrels have
another thing coming.

21
00:00:54,290 --> 00:00:55,860
- Unbelievable.
- Honey, wait!

22
00:00:56,760 --> 00:01:00,430
What now? What do we do about this?

23
00:01:01,230 --> 00:01:03,030
You've got to be kidding me.

24
00:01:04,270 --> 00:01:07,970
Where is everyone?
Get out here, now!

25
00:01:08,340 --> 00:01:12,640
I'm going to settle this
once and for all today.

26
00:01:12,810 --> 00:01:13,880
What is this?

27
00:01:13,880 --> 00:01:14,950
Let go of me.

28
00:01:15,010 --> 00:01:16,680
What brings you all the way here?

29
00:01:18,750 --> 00:01:21,650
Yesterday, you treated my daughter
like a thief,

30
00:01:22,020 --> 00:01:23,860
and now you're actually
turning her into one.

31
00:01:24,160 --> 00:01:25,860
What are you talking about?

32
00:01:26,120 --> 00:01:30,200
I know my Yu Na is head over heels
for this punk, but still.

33
00:01:31,260 --> 00:01:34,500
How dare you use her feelings
to try and snatch up our stocks?

34
00:01:37,300 --> 00:01:40,540
Yu Na ran off
with my husband's seal...

35
00:01:41,340 --> 00:01:43,270
to hand over our shares to you.

36
00:01:43,270 --> 00:01:45,440
You two are teaming up to ruin us.

37
00:01:47,080 --> 00:01:49,110
Ms. Choi is signing over
your shares?

38
00:02:09,130 --> 00:02:11,740
I need some time
to get everything together.

39
00:02:12,300 --> 00:02:13,300
Get everything together?

40
00:02:13,740 --> 00:02:15,440
I've already taken care of it.

41
00:02:16,810 --> 00:02:19,680
The shares are
in your father's name, right?

42
00:02:20,080 --> 00:02:22,580
I've got the power of attorney
and transfer papers ready,

43
00:02:23,150 --> 00:02:25,380
so just bring your father's seal.

44
00:02:26,680 --> 00:02:28,650
If you try anything
and drag your feet,

45
00:02:29,020 --> 00:02:31,390
I'll tell the chairman
as soon as he's off work.

46
00:02:32,420 --> 00:02:36,030
Stop scheming and get to work.

47
00:02:57,120 --> 00:03:00,250
She's handing the stocks over
to the chairman's wife.

48
00:03:02,750 --> 00:03:04,390
If Choi Yu Na loses the stocks,

49
00:03:05,420 --> 00:03:06,860
it wouldn't be so bad for me.

50
00:03:22,240 --> 00:03:23,240
Excuse me.

51
00:03:23,510 --> 00:03:25,810
Chloe is the victim
in this incident.

52
00:03:25,810 --> 00:03:28,110
We ask that you refrain
from any speculative reporting.

53
00:03:28,310 --> 00:03:29,310
Let's go.

54
00:03:31,020 --> 00:03:33,590
So, no, I don't want to thank you.

55
00:03:34,420 --> 00:03:37,520
I'll repay you for your help
some other way.

56
00:03:51,670 --> 00:03:55,310
You little brat,
is your phone just an accessory?

57
00:03:55,710 --> 00:03:57,940
Why on earth isn't she picking up?
Seriously.

58
00:04:02,180 --> 00:04:04,220
(Chloe)

59
00:04:09,020 --> 00:04:11,220
I can't really talk right now.

60
00:04:11,860 --> 00:04:12,860
Why not?

61
00:04:13,160 --> 00:04:16,360
Is it because Ms. Choi is about
to sign over her father's shares?

62
00:04:17,700 --> 00:04:19,560
Wait, how do you know that?

63
00:04:20,570 --> 00:04:23,230
Ms. Choi just went
inside your house.

64
00:04:23,840 --> 00:04:25,340
If you don't act fast and stop her,

65
00:04:25,970 --> 00:04:27,570
all her family's shares...

66
00:04:28,210 --> 00:04:29,940
will go to the chairman's wife.

67
00:04:39,920 --> 00:04:42,750
(Stock Transfer Agreement)

68
00:04:56,670 --> 00:04:59,840
Are you sure
you took care of everything?

69
00:05:00,540 --> 00:05:04,310
Come on.
You saw that accuser guy confess.

70
00:05:04,740 --> 00:05:07,650
I even made him keep his mouth shut
and promised to tie up loose ends.

71
00:05:08,180 --> 00:05:11,420
After all that,
the least you can do is stamp it.

72
00:05:16,120 --> 00:05:17,120
Here.

73
00:05:22,630 --> 00:05:24,030
(Grantor: Choi Sam Sik)

74
00:05:26,860 --> 00:05:28,000
(Grantor: Choi Sam Sik)

75
00:05:31,840 --> 00:05:33,770
(Grantor: Choi Sam Sik)

76
00:05:55,490 --> 00:05:56,590
You...

77
00:05:56,790 --> 00:05:59,230
What do you think you're doing?

78
00:06:02,070 --> 00:06:03,570
Right back at you.

79
00:06:04,300 --> 00:06:07,340
What are you two plotting?

80
00:06:10,880 --> 00:06:14,980
Did she promise you anything
in return for the shares,

81
00:06:18,780 --> 00:06:20,320
or have you already received it?

82
00:06:21,390 --> 00:06:24,960
What? Why are you on our case?

83
00:06:25,460 --> 00:06:29,090
This was a mutual agreement.
Mind your own business.

84
00:06:30,360 --> 00:06:31,860
A mutual agreement?

85
00:06:32,730 --> 00:06:35,830
The actual owner of the shares
certainly didn't agree.

86
00:06:38,440 --> 00:06:41,370
- Choi Yu Na, you little brat!
- Mom?

87
00:06:42,040 --> 00:06:46,380
Wait, where is it?
You... I can't believe you.

88
00:06:47,480 --> 00:06:51,450
Of course it was
this piece of trash's doing.

89
00:06:52,350 --> 00:06:54,950
I should've known from the moment
you grabbed my hair.

90
00:06:55,290 --> 00:06:58,290
How dare you try to steal
our precious shares?

91
00:06:59,690 --> 00:07:01,290
- Goodness.
- Unbelievable.

92
00:07:02,090 --> 00:07:05,530
I didn't force her into this deal.
Your daughter agreed to it.

93
00:07:05,730 --> 00:07:06,730
What?

94
00:07:06,830 --> 00:07:10,400
Ms. Choi, explain.
Why aren't you saying anything?

95
00:07:14,270 --> 00:07:15,440
- What...
- Wait.

96
00:07:15,740 --> 00:07:18,940
Where do you think you're going?
Hey!

97
00:07:19,540 --> 00:07:21,810
This isn't over between us.
You got that?

98
00:07:22,950 --> 00:07:26,820
You brat! Choi Yu Na, get back here!
I can't believe you.

99
00:07:28,190 --> 00:07:29,690
Are you kidding me?

100
00:07:30,320 --> 00:07:31,990
Who are you to mess up a done deal?

101
00:07:33,460 --> 00:07:36,860
You're the one
who sabotaged me first.

102
00:07:43,500 --> 00:07:44,900
Get in here, you little brat.

103
00:07:46,900 --> 00:07:48,440
You've lost your darn mind.

104
00:07:49,540 --> 00:07:52,810
Even if they offered you shares
to get you to marry Min Jun,

105
00:07:52,880 --> 00:07:54,880
you should be offended by that.

106
00:07:55,280 --> 00:07:59,720
Why would you hand our shares over
to that useless witch?

107
00:07:59,820 --> 00:08:02,620
What did that old fox say
to manipulate you?

108
00:08:03,190 --> 00:08:06,990
- I had my reasons. I had to do it.
- What?

109
00:08:07,020 --> 00:08:10,330
Couldn't you just trust
that I had my reasons?

110
00:08:10,760 --> 00:08:13,130
Are those stupid shares
really that important to you?

111
00:08:13,200 --> 00:08:17,170
My gosh. You've completely
lost your mind, haven't you?

112
00:08:17,270 --> 00:08:19,800
Maybe you need some sense
beaten into you.

113
00:08:19,870 --> 00:08:21,710
Honey, no!

114
00:08:22,110 --> 00:08:23,210
Please calm down.

115
00:08:23,710 --> 00:08:26,980
Yu Na, hurry up
and tell us what's going on,

116
00:08:27,040 --> 00:08:28,410
and beg for forgiveness.

117
00:08:29,010 --> 00:08:31,780
- Why do I have to apologize?
- My word.

118
00:08:32,120 --> 00:08:34,320
- You...
- I'm the victim here.

119
00:08:34,950 --> 00:08:37,620
I was heartbroken
after Park Min Jun dumped me,

120
00:08:37,820 --> 00:08:40,690
and then I was blackmailed
by some cowardly con artist.

121
00:08:40,860 --> 00:08:43,290
Goodness. What in the world...

122
00:08:43,360 --> 00:08:45,430
is she even talking about right now?

123
00:08:45,660 --> 00:08:48,430
Wait. A con artist
behind the accusation?

124
00:08:49,070 --> 00:08:50,900
Did you have anything to do
with the accusation...

125
00:08:50,900 --> 00:08:52,140
that caused such an uproar?

126
00:08:53,910 --> 00:08:56,210
That's right. Yes.

127
00:08:56,940 --> 00:09:00,380
I stole the design book
and told him what lies to tell.

128
00:09:00,540 --> 00:09:02,250
- You did what?
- What?

129
00:09:03,410 --> 00:09:06,320
If I hadn't acted,
people would've found out it was me.

130
00:09:08,020 --> 00:09:11,490
I had no choice
after that con artist blackmailed me.

131
00:09:12,190 --> 00:09:14,930
I had to give up our shares
if I wanted this to go away...

132
00:09:14,990 --> 00:09:17,960
and stay at Adele
for a second chance.

133
00:09:17,960 --> 00:09:19,160
My gosh.

134
00:09:19,230 --> 00:09:21,700
- Goodness me.
- Oh, dear.

135
00:09:22,030 --> 00:09:23,030
What...

136
00:09:23,530 --> 00:09:24,740
What are we going to do?

137
00:09:26,270 --> 00:09:30,340
So hand over the shares.
I mean, your seal.

138
00:09:30,810 --> 00:09:33,410
I need to hand over our shares
to the chairman's wife.

139
00:09:33,880 --> 00:09:35,010
Come on!

140
00:09:35,580 --> 00:09:37,450
Hand it over!

141
00:09:37,520 --> 00:09:41,220
Unbelievable.
Are you out of your mind?

142
00:09:41,690 --> 00:09:45,460
- My gosh!
- Oh no, what do we do?

143
00:09:45,520 --> 00:09:47,590
She's gone completely insane.

144
00:09:48,030 --> 00:09:50,730
- My gosh.
- Gosh, I can't believe this.

145
00:10:06,010 --> 00:10:08,410
Looks like you
got everything sorted out.

146
00:10:08,750 --> 00:10:12,050
Yes, thanks to you, we managed
to sort it out just in time.

147
00:10:12,150 --> 00:10:13,280
Thank you.

148
00:10:15,490 --> 00:10:16,950
Thanks for your help.

149
00:10:20,390 --> 00:10:23,030
You were a huge help, Chloe.

150
00:10:23,330 --> 00:10:25,100
If Ms. Oh had gotten her hands
on those shares...

151
00:10:26,100 --> 00:10:27,870
I don't even want to think about it.

152
00:10:33,140 --> 00:10:36,270
There's no need to thank me.

153
00:10:36,910 --> 00:10:39,540
I was suspicious
about Ms. Choi's share transfer,

154
00:10:39,780 --> 00:10:43,250
so I stopped it in case
it was connected to recent events.

155
00:10:47,220 --> 00:10:48,850
This confirms it.

156
00:10:50,150 --> 00:10:54,330
Choi Yu Na stole the design book
and is behind the false accusation.

157
00:10:55,130 --> 00:10:57,360
Ms. Oh must be using that
as leverage,

158
00:10:57,360 --> 00:10:59,600
since Yu Na was giving up the shares
for free.

159
00:11:00,230 --> 00:11:01,870
For free?

160
00:11:03,000 --> 00:11:06,970
Just because no money changed hands
doesn't mean she got nothing back.

161
00:11:08,040 --> 00:11:11,280
Jung Ran could be helping
the accuser disappear...

162
00:11:11,280 --> 00:11:13,780
completely off the grid,

163
00:11:13,780 --> 00:11:16,450
or she could've forced him
to make a false confession.

164
00:11:17,620 --> 00:11:20,580
Simply put, you think the accuser
was held captive somewhere...

165
00:11:20,650 --> 00:11:22,750
and was forced to make
a false confession.

166
00:11:23,320 --> 00:11:25,620
Yu Na couldn't have done it alone,

167
00:11:25,860 --> 00:11:29,660
but someone like the chairman's wife
could easily pull it off.

168
00:11:32,600 --> 00:11:36,430
If Ms. Oh's really keeping him
locked up like you said, ma'am,

169
00:11:36,770 --> 00:11:39,640
wouldn't he be in serious trouble?

170
00:11:40,240 --> 00:11:44,810
She might do something terrible
to silence him for good.

171
00:11:45,510 --> 00:11:49,280
Ask the police to move
quickly and discreetly.

172
00:11:50,280 --> 00:11:51,280
Sure.

173
00:11:51,620 --> 00:11:54,350
And keep a closer eye
on Ms. Choi and the chairman's wife.

174
00:11:54,720 --> 00:11:56,390
Right, I'm on it.

175
00:12:07,870 --> 00:12:10,530
Is President Kim always like that?

176
00:12:12,300 --> 00:12:13,500
What do you mean?

177
00:12:14,670 --> 00:12:17,980
She just seems incredibly skilled...

178
00:12:18,610 --> 00:12:19,980
at handling a crisis.

179
00:12:20,910 --> 00:12:23,580
Has she always been that way?

180
00:12:28,790 --> 00:12:30,120
Has she always been like that?

181
00:12:31,220 --> 00:12:32,690
I can't say for sure.

182
00:12:33,920 --> 00:12:37,390
I don't know what she was like
before I was born.

183
00:12:39,600 --> 00:12:41,800
But for as long as I can remember,

184
00:12:42,300 --> 00:12:43,970
my mother has always been fighting.

185
00:12:44,770 --> 00:12:48,210
Fighting against hostile people
and judgmental stares,

186
00:12:49,010 --> 00:12:50,110
even to this day.

187
00:12:50,340 --> 00:12:51,810
What for?

188
00:12:52,340 --> 00:12:54,810
To take over Adele Group?

189
00:12:58,080 --> 00:12:59,420
I'm not trying to be critical.

190
00:13:00,080 --> 00:13:03,090
I'm genuinely curious this time.

191
00:13:04,790 --> 00:13:06,820
I was just wondering
what kind of goal...

192
00:13:07,320 --> 00:13:09,590
could drive someone to fight...

193
00:13:10,460 --> 00:13:11,460
so relentlessly.

194
00:13:13,600 --> 00:13:15,070
The biggest reason...

195
00:13:15,800 --> 00:13:17,030
was probably me.

196
00:13:20,070 --> 00:13:21,070
Maybe not.

197
00:13:21,840 --> 00:13:25,040
She might claim
it's to protect her son,

198
00:13:25,240 --> 00:13:26,410
but her real motive...

199
00:13:26,480 --> 00:13:29,110
could be taking over Adele Group.

200
00:13:35,150 --> 00:13:37,720
I used to think that, too.

201
00:13:38,420 --> 00:13:40,690
You must become
the head of Adele Group.

202
00:13:42,090 --> 00:13:44,560
I really thought you were different.

203
00:13:46,300 --> 00:13:48,070
But you're just like the rest
of them, aren't you?

204
00:13:49,700 --> 00:13:51,040
You don't want to protect me.

205
00:13:51,040 --> 00:13:52,540
You were just using me...

206
00:13:53,700 --> 00:13:55,170
to take over the company.

207
00:13:57,910 --> 00:14:00,280
After regretting my actions
for so long,

208
00:14:00,380 --> 00:14:02,010
I started to think more about
what she said.

209
00:14:03,310 --> 00:14:06,450
Why did my mother want
Adele Group so badly?

210
00:14:07,520 --> 00:14:11,690
Was it her way of making amends
by ensuring I had a place,

211
00:14:12,860 --> 00:14:15,430
since I was born out of wedlock?

212
00:14:16,490 --> 00:14:19,530
An illegitimate son
who has no place?

213
00:14:23,130 --> 00:14:26,900
They subtly look down on me
for being an illegitimate son.

214
00:14:27,340 --> 00:14:28,970
Illegitimate? Seriously?

215
00:14:29,410 --> 00:14:32,480
You should've gotten that crazy idea
out of your head immediately.

216
00:14:32,910 --> 00:14:36,710
From now on, if you get bad ideas,
you come straight to me.

217
00:14:37,010 --> 00:14:41,820
I'll remind you
how precious and perfect you are.

218
00:14:47,060 --> 00:14:49,090
You're still...

219
00:14:50,130 --> 00:14:51,360
If...

220
00:14:52,130 --> 00:14:54,060
you were Jin Ju,

221
00:14:54,270 --> 00:14:56,100
you'd probably lecture me...

222
00:14:56,970 --> 00:14:58,770
for still thinking this way.

223
00:15:09,910 --> 00:15:11,180
You are a precious...

224
00:15:12,480 --> 00:15:14,250
and perfect person.

225
00:15:18,120 --> 00:15:22,090
If you're the reason President Kim
has been fighting all this time,

226
00:15:23,830 --> 00:15:25,960
it's not because
you were illegitimate.

227
00:15:27,060 --> 00:15:29,700
It's because
you're her precious and perfect son.

228
00:15:31,800 --> 00:15:33,700
That must've made her want
to protect you even more.

229
00:16:01,830 --> 00:16:05,300
My wife and Ms. Choi
were trying to trade shares?

230
00:16:05,600 --> 00:16:08,170
Kim Myung Hui found out
and put a stop to it?

231
00:16:08,870 --> 00:16:13,140
Yes. That's what our people
watching Kim Myung Hui reported.

232
00:16:14,380 --> 00:16:18,080
They're all running wild
behind my back.

233
00:16:18,550 --> 00:16:22,050
Since the deal didn't go through,
we didn't take any further action.

234
00:16:24,190 --> 00:16:26,460
How much did Ms. Choi ask
for the shares?

235
00:16:26,920 --> 00:16:29,860
We weren't able to confirm that.
However,

236
00:16:30,790 --> 00:16:34,160
it seems this all happened
without Choi Sam Sik's consent.

237
00:16:35,900 --> 00:16:37,700
Is she so desperate for money...

238
00:16:37,700 --> 00:16:41,040
that she has to sell
her father's shares behind his back?

239
00:16:42,240 --> 00:16:45,140
Or maybe there was another side
to the deal.

240
00:16:46,040 --> 00:16:47,610
Shall I bring in Ms. Choi?

241
00:16:49,380 --> 00:16:50,380
Before you do,

242
00:16:51,850 --> 00:16:53,920
I need to get my own family
in order first.

243
00:16:58,820 --> 00:17:00,020
Kim Myung Hui!

244
00:17:02,230 --> 00:17:04,360
That miserable tramp.

245
00:17:04,700 --> 00:17:06,400
How did she find out
and track us down...

246
00:17:06,400 --> 00:17:07,500
just to ruin everything?

247
00:17:08,630 --> 00:17:09,870
My head is killing me.

248
00:17:09,870 --> 00:17:12,670
Mrs. Ok, get me an aspirin!

249
00:17:21,080 --> 00:17:22,810
There you go again.

250
00:17:23,410 --> 00:17:25,380
Didn't I tell you
to watch your expression?

251
00:17:26,280 --> 00:17:29,650
I'm so furious I could pass out,
and you're standing there smiling?

252
00:17:29,790 --> 00:17:32,820
Don't you think that would make
my blood boil enough to kill me?

253
00:17:34,120 --> 00:17:35,760
You've got it wrong again.

254
00:17:35,760 --> 00:17:37,760
I was born with this smiley face,

255
00:17:37,830 --> 00:17:40,030
so I told you I can't help it.

256
00:17:40,130 --> 00:17:41,430
Even at your funeral,

257
00:17:41,500 --> 00:17:44,100
I'd probably be smiling
at your photo.

258
00:17:45,000 --> 00:17:46,340
Just go on and take your medicine.

259
00:17:49,470 --> 00:17:51,180
You!

260
00:17:52,310 --> 00:17:53,310
What now?

261
00:17:54,010 --> 00:17:55,450
Sir, you're home.

262
00:17:57,780 --> 00:17:59,220
Why you...

263
00:18:00,650 --> 00:18:02,520
Get dinner ready.

264
00:18:02,950 --> 00:18:05,020
We'll all be eating
together tonight.

265
00:18:05,390 --> 00:18:06,390
Yes, sir.

266
00:18:36,690 --> 00:18:37,860
What is it, Mom?

267
00:18:37,860 --> 00:18:40,120
Why waste energy
huffing and puffing again?

268
00:18:41,020 --> 00:18:42,460
I can't stand it.

269
00:18:43,260 --> 00:18:47,260
This tramp and that witch.
I can't stand any of them.

270
00:18:50,270 --> 00:18:52,000
My point exactly.

271
00:18:52,900 --> 00:18:56,240
What's all this fuss
about the shares owned...

272
00:18:57,140 --> 00:18:58,610
by Ms. Choi's father?

273
00:19:01,010 --> 00:19:02,580
What? What's going on?

274
00:19:04,650 --> 00:19:06,020
Am I the only one
out of the loop here?

275
00:19:07,550 --> 00:19:08,950
As for Ms. Choi's father's shares,

276
00:19:09,850 --> 00:19:12,420
- once she marries Min Jun...
- I'm calling off...

277
00:19:13,860 --> 00:19:15,560
their wedding.

278
00:19:18,730 --> 00:19:21,030
Min Jun himself doesn't want this,

279
00:19:21,030 --> 00:19:25,640
and I can't approve of Ms. Choi
as his partner.

280
00:19:27,570 --> 00:19:29,540
I'm the one
who approves things around here!

281
00:19:35,680 --> 00:19:39,680
You think being president is enough
and you don't need the shares,

282
00:19:39,980 --> 00:19:41,420
but one word from me...

283
00:19:42,250 --> 00:19:43,950
and you're out at any moment.

284
00:19:44,450 --> 00:19:45,460
Father.

285
00:19:50,560 --> 00:19:52,630
Pull yourselves together.

286
00:19:53,800 --> 00:19:57,070
I make all the decisions
in this family. Period.

287
00:19:58,300 --> 00:20:00,500
As long as I back Ms. Choi,

288
00:20:00,870 --> 00:20:02,310
the wedding will happen,

289
00:20:03,210 --> 00:20:04,940
and I'll get...

290
00:20:05,510 --> 00:20:06,940
her father's shares.

291
00:20:08,450 --> 00:20:10,680
- You?
- That's right.

292
00:20:11,780 --> 00:20:15,590
All shares of the Adele Group
rightfully belong to me.

293
00:20:19,460 --> 00:20:21,090
The wedding will proceed as planned,

294
00:20:23,360 --> 00:20:26,730
and don't even think about
touching Ms. Choi's shares.

295
00:20:53,820 --> 00:20:56,730
What is it?
You still have something to say?

296
00:20:56,990 --> 00:20:59,500
I'm not going to marry her.

297
00:21:00,630 --> 00:21:02,670
Were you not listening
to a word I said?

298
00:21:02,670 --> 00:21:06,470
It's my marriage.
It's not your decision to make.

299
00:21:07,500 --> 00:21:10,340
And stop using my marriage...

300
00:21:11,040 --> 00:21:13,010
to threaten my mother.

301
00:21:13,010 --> 00:21:15,510
It wasn't a threat.
It was a reality check.

302
00:21:17,550 --> 00:21:20,680
If you refuse to marry
and get on my bad side,

303
00:21:20,950 --> 00:21:23,790
she'll lose her position anyway.

304
00:21:24,120 --> 00:21:26,990
She kept her position this time
by bringing Chloe on board,

305
00:21:28,160 --> 00:21:31,160
but without my support,

306
00:21:31,460 --> 00:21:33,430
she'll be pushed out.

307
00:21:37,900 --> 00:21:39,540
Is that all...

308
00:21:40,070 --> 00:21:41,670
my mother means to you?

309
00:21:42,570 --> 00:21:46,540
She's stood by you for years,
working harder than anyone...

310
00:21:46,640 --> 00:21:48,650
for Adele.

311
00:21:49,480 --> 00:21:53,180
Can't you protect her,
if only for her loyalty?

312
00:21:55,850 --> 00:21:56,920
My first priority...

313
00:21:58,560 --> 00:22:00,060
is to protect Adele...

314
00:22:01,930 --> 00:22:04,390
and keep my family in line.

315
00:22:04,390 --> 00:22:06,500
Don't hide behind the company!

316
00:22:08,170 --> 00:22:09,530
In the end, everything you do...

317
00:22:10,530 --> 00:22:12,500
is driven
by your own selfish ambition.

318
00:22:13,800 --> 00:22:16,240
You're just as selfish.

319
00:22:17,640 --> 00:22:20,480
You're selfishly refusing
to get married,

320
00:22:20,910 --> 00:22:22,210
and you dare to blame me?

321
00:22:22,210 --> 00:22:23,450
Father!

322
00:22:24,410 --> 00:22:25,420
Min Jun.

323
00:22:37,130 --> 00:22:40,160
Stop making a scene
about this marriage...

324
00:22:40,460 --> 00:22:41,670
and talk some sense into him.

325
00:22:46,040 --> 00:22:47,970
Aren't you going to answer me?

326
00:22:55,110 --> 00:22:58,950
For Min Jun's sake,
please, reconsider.

327
00:23:00,420 --> 00:23:02,490
That is my answer, sir.

328
00:23:27,240 --> 00:23:28,310
I put you in a tight spot.

329
00:23:30,250 --> 00:23:31,250
I'm so sorry.

330
00:23:36,420 --> 00:23:38,960
You're always apologizing,

331
00:23:40,760 --> 00:23:43,130
even though I'm the one
who should be sorry.

332
00:23:45,400 --> 00:23:46,830
It was my choices...

333
00:23:47,760 --> 00:23:50,170
that brought you
into the Adele family.

334
00:23:51,870 --> 00:23:53,640
And because I wasn't strong enough,

335
00:23:55,310 --> 00:23:57,740
I've made you carry this burden.

336
00:24:02,110 --> 00:24:05,180
Why did it have to be Father?

337
00:24:07,780 --> 00:24:09,920
I've always wanted to ask you.

338
00:24:09,920 --> 00:24:12,020
Why him? Why did you make...

339
00:24:13,220 --> 00:24:14,860
that choice?

340
00:24:22,300 --> 00:24:24,130
Because I had to protect you.

341
00:24:29,210 --> 00:24:32,110
I think that's why I did it.

342
00:24:47,460 --> 00:24:50,560
We'll figure this out.

343
00:24:52,530 --> 00:24:55,170
The false accusation,
this forced marriage,

344
00:24:57,970 --> 00:24:59,800
and any hardships we face
in this family.

345
00:25:05,310 --> 00:25:06,610
Thank you, my son.

346
00:25:26,160 --> 00:25:29,700
So, you got caught trying to snatch
Choi Yu Na's shares?

347
00:25:30,470 --> 00:25:32,300
I'm telling you,
it was a legitimate transaction.

348
00:25:33,900 --> 00:25:35,170
How much were you offering?

349
00:25:35,470 --> 00:25:36,970
It's better if you don't know.

350
00:25:37,070 --> 00:25:38,440
Knowing too much can get you hurt.

351
00:25:39,340 --> 00:25:41,480
Honestly, Ms. Oh.

352
00:25:41,780 --> 00:25:43,050
Really, Mom?

353
00:25:44,920 --> 00:25:46,580
You know how terrifying
Father can be, right?

354
00:25:47,220 --> 00:25:49,920
He already warned you they were his.
If you try to take them again,

355
00:25:51,550 --> 00:25:53,620
you're going to get seriously hurt.

356
00:25:55,160 --> 00:25:57,860
I'm not kidding.
I'm worried about you.

357
00:25:58,560 --> 00:26:00,660
Look at my son,
all worried about his mother.

358
00:26:01,260 --> 00:26:02,430
Don't you worry.

359
00:26:03,970 --> 00:26:07,400
I've already weighed my options
and decided to back off.

360
00:26:20,220 --> 00:26:21,220
What?

361
00:26:21,620 --> 00:26:24,350
Wait, the shares are one thing,
but the plan is another.

362
00:26:24,420 --> 00:26:26,660
You're changing the whole plan
because you didn't get the stocks?

363
00:26:30,860 --> 00:26:34,560
Wasn't the plan to lock him up
until you got the shares,

364
00:26:34,660 --> 00:26:38,570
wear him down, and then
pay him off to take the fall?

365
00:26:40,740 --> 00:26:41,740
Please don't tell me...

366
00:26:46,580 --> 00:26:49,180
you're planning to kill again.

367
00:26:50,010 --> 00:26:52,080
Killing him would be
too much of a hassle.

368
00:26:52,520 --> 00:26:54,990
It's much cleaner to find a buyer
and get him off our hands.

369
00:26:55,420 --> 00:26:59,260
If we hand him over to traffickers,
we get a nice payout...

370
00:26:59,320 --> 00:27:02,530
and don't have to worry
about cleaning up any messes.

371
00:27:02,530 --> 00:27:04,230
Jung Ran!

372
00:27:04,790 --> 00:27:06,530
Why are you yelling?

373
00:27:07,860 --> 00:27:11,270
I can't have a good day
if my brows aren't perfect.

374
00:27:11,670 --> 00:27:13,240
Enough with the lecture.

375
00:27:13,240 --> 00:27:14,800
Just do your job and watch him.

376
00:27:25,050 --> 00:27:27,320
(Kim Myung Hui, Park Tae Ho,
Oh Jung Ran, Park Min Jun)

377
00:27:30,850 --> 00:27:32,060
(Oh Jung Ran)

378
00:27:32,120 --> 00:27:35,060
Oh Jung Ran,
the chairman's wife at Adele.

379
00:27:36,390 --> 00:27:39,830
I thought all she did was manage
Chairman Park Tae Ho's slush fund,

380
00:27:40,930 --> 00:27:43,470
but she's much more dangerous
than I thought.

381
00:27:44,430 --> 00:27:47,170
She'd kidnap someone
just to get her hands on some shares...

382
00:27:47,640 --> 00:27:49,210
and even hold them captive.

383
00:27:49,310 --> 00:27:50,770
Tell me about it.

384
00:27:51,980 --> 00:27:55,380
When you think about it,
that family is pretty lucky.

385
00:27:56,010 --> 00:27:58,250
The parents are so wicked
and ruthless,

386
00:27:58,520 --> 00:28:00,620
but their two sons,
Park Min Jun and Park Hyun Jun,

387
00:28:01,120 --> 00:28:02,320
turned out completely normal.

388
00:28:04,450 --> 00:28:07,060
You can't tell
just from how they seem.

389
00:28:07,120 --> 00:28:08,360
(Park Min Jun, Park Hyun Jun)

390
00:28:08,430 --> 00:28:09,690
I'm sure...

391
00:28:10,530 --> 00:28:12,860
they're both dealing
with a lot of pain you can't see.

392
00:28:14,760 --> 00:28:17,230
Are you worried
about their pain now?

393
00:28:18,770 --> 00:28:20,170
Worried? Hardly.

394
00:28:21,970 --> 00:28:24,570
Not when I can barely handle
my own pain.

395
00:28:28,310 --> 00:28:31,210
Have you found a way for me
to get close to Oh Jung Ran?

396
00:28:31,820 --> 00:28:32,820
Sure.

397
00:28:33,780 --> 00:28:34,920
Every Thursday,

398
00:28:35,620 --> 00:28:38,020
she eats with Director Seo.

399
00:28:41,290 --> 00:28:43,060
(Oh Jung Ran)

400
00:28:50,030 --> 00:28:52,440
They share company intel
and plot their next move.

401
00:28:52,440 --> 00:28:53,900
The people who are on our side...

402
00:28:54,170 --> 00:28:55,540
If you're planning
a "chance" encounter,

403
00:28:55,540 --> 00:28:56,940
this is your moment.

404
00:28:57,170 --> 00:29:00,410
- But it's not that easy.
- Still trying, are you?

405
00:29:00,740 --> 00:29:04,080
You've been at it this long
and still don't have enough?

406
00:29:04,450 --> 00:29:06,780
Director Baek,
how can you eat right now?

407
00:29:06,780 --> 00:29:08,250
Put those chopsticks down.

408
00:29:08,850 --> 00:29:09,990
I'm talking here.

409
00:29:14,320 --> 00:29:15,790
Don't you think that's pathetic?

410
00:29:17,160 --> 00:29:18,460
I need to eat to think straight.

411
00:29:18,460 --> 00:29:20,500
Unbelievable.

412
00:29:20,560 --> 00:29:22,300
You should be focused on work.

413
00:29:25,240 --> 00:29:26,240
Goodness.

414
00:29:31,340 --> 00:29:32,380
Quick question.

415
00:29:33,280 --> 00:29:35,510
Why do you want to get close
to Oh Jung Ran?

416
00:29:41,580 --> 00:29:44,020
(Oh Jung Ran)

417
00:29:44,090 --> 00:29:46,860
I need to deal
with the false accusation.

418
00:29:47,220 --> 00:29:49,130
Thanks to Oh Jung Ran's
interference,

419
00:29:49,690 --> 00:29:53,830
it's now clear that the key witness
is being held captive.

420
00:29:54,760 --> 00:29:58,870
I'll find him and make him testify
about what Choi Yu Na did.

421
00:30:00,270 --> 00:30:02,140
Do you have a plan?

422
00:30:03,370 --> 00:30:04,370
Yes.

423
00:30:05,610 --> 00:30:07,410
I'm going to use the same tactic...

424
00:30:08,680 --> 00:30:10,080
Choi Yu Na used.

425
00:30:12,820 --> 00:30:14,850
(Oh Jung Ran)

426
00:30:19,220 --> 00:30:20,520
Why are you calling again?

427
00:30:20,920 --> 00:30:23,690
The stock deal is dead,
so why pay hush money?

428
00:30:24,360 --> 00:30:26,030
That's enough.
Stop bothering me with these calls.

429
00:30:29,400 --> 00:30:31,070
- What the...
- My gosh.

430
00:30:31,070 --> 00:30:32,340
I'm so sorry.

431
00:30:32,400 --> 00:30:33,400
Seriously.

432
00:30:34,300 --> 00:30:35,540
Ms. Oh?

433
00:30:38,070 --> 00:30:41,580
We briefly met when you came
to see Ms. Choi.

434
00:30:42,450 --> 00:30:44,750
I'm Chloe, a consultant
in the bio division.

435
00:30:46,050 --> 00:30:48,950
Right. The one Kim Myung Hui hired.

436
00:30:49,820 --> 00:30:50,820
Yes.

437
00:30:51,620 --> 00:30:54,720
Oh no, I've stained your clothes.
I'm so sorry.

438
00:30:55,860 --> 00:30:57,390
Let me get that for you.

439
00:30:57,730 --> 00:31:00,060
Wait, what are you doing?

440
00:31:03,600 --> 00:31:05,000
I said it's fine.

441
00:31:06,940 --> 00:31:08,910
I'm so sorry. How clumsy of me.

442
00:31:09,740 --> 00:31:11,210
You should wash your hands.

443
00:31:11,740 --> 00:31:12,740
Unbelievable.

444
00:31:17,850 --> 00:31:20,950
I guess I was just really nervous
being around you.

445
00:31:21,680 --> 00:31:24,050
I'm not usually this nervous,
even around President Kim.

446
00:31:24,650 --> 00:31:26,620
You just have
such a strong presence.

447
00:31:29,860 --> 00:31:31,530
A strong presence?

448
00:31:33,100 --> 00:31:36,130
You mean something like charisma?

449
00:31:36,470 --> 00:31:39,840
Exactly. You seemed extraordinary
from the moment I saw you.

450
00:31:40,500 --> 00:31:41,500
Of course.

451
00:31:42,270 --> 00:31:44,440
I hear you're good at what you do.
You've got a good eye.

452
00:31:57,290 --> 00:31:58,290
Hold on.

453
00:32:34,920 --> 00:32:37,860
(Pearl in Red)

454
00:32:38,090 --> 00:32:40,600
If she kidnapped someone
and held him captive,

455
00:32:40,600 --> 00:32:42,670
she must've had help.

456
00:32:42,970 --> 00:32:46,200
Let's track her communications
and see who contacts her.

457
00:32:46,300 --> 00:32:48,200
President Kim Myung Hui
has my jacket?

458
00:32:48,740 --> 00:32:50,510
How? I'm sure I threw it away.

459
00:32:50,810 --> 00:32:52,580
What's this about an informant?

460
00:32:52,810 --> 00:32:54,410
If the police get
their hands on that...

461
00:32:54,540 --> 00:32:55,610
What?

462
00:32:55,610 --> 00:32:57,710
You can back out if it's too much.

463
00:32:57,750 --> 00:33:00,380
If there's anything I can do,
I have to at least try.

464
00:33:00,420 --> 00:33:03,520
I have to stop Ms. Oh
before things get worse.

465
00:33:04,750 --> 00:33:06,760
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
